2001-07-04  uid24111
	* src/DC/i_system.c:
	* src/SDL/i_video.c:
	* src/X11/i_video.c:
	* src/i_main.c:
	* src/i_video.h:
	* src/m_misc.c:
		Implemented dubblebuffering, it works, I don't have any tearing now and in some modes it's even faster than without doublebuffering.
		But there is still a problem and I don't know if it's a PrBoom or SDL problem.
		When I tried 1024x768, the the statusbar background isn't drawn when using double buffering.
		I don't understand this, because I draw everything to a backbuffer and then copy it in one block to the screen backbuffer.
		When I tried 1024x600 (still uses 1024x768 mode), I got a crash when doing the wipe.
		Maybe there are some bugs which now show up.

