2001-04-18  cph
	* src/g_game.c:
		Add new version number for demo recording
		Change total time calculation to discard fractions of seconds,
		 so our episode timings match those of Compet-n

2001-04-15  cph
	* doc/README.demos:
	* src/doomstat.h:
	* src/doomtype.h:
	* src/g_game.c:
	* src/p_mobj.c:
		Add a pile of new compatibility levels, including doom v1.2 compatibility
		Most importantly, separate compatibility levels for doom2 v1.9 and
		 ultimate/final doom/doom95 v1.9
		New G_GetOriginalDoomCompatLevel which guesses which of the above we
		 should used, based on the IWAD loaded or -complevel
		Couple of new compatibility options
		 - comp_soul - controls whether charging lost souls bounce
		 - comp_666 - controls whether 666 tags work at non-ExM8 levels ala doom v1.2
		Upgrade G_Compatibility so it can be used at any compatibility level,
		 overriding only those options which the target engine didn't know about
		Code changes in p_mobj.c to implement the improved bouncing-lost-soul
		 compatibility
		Update documentation

	* src/p_doors.c:
	* src/p_floor.c:
		A couple of compatibility fixes from the stable branch

2001-04-05  cph
	* src/p_doors.c:
		In orignial doom, if a DR door is triggered that already has a floor/lighting
		 action in progress, we don't do the door but corrupt the existing action
		 instead. Added compatibility. cf ep1-0511.lmp. Thanks to Adam Williamson
		 for pointing me to it.

