2000-10-05  proff_fs
	* src/d_main.c:
	* src/gl_main.c:
	* src/gl_texture.c:
	* src/p_setup.c:
		Started to use vertex arrays. More work needs to be done to use them efficiently, but that's not much from now on.
		Some other small fixes.

2000-10-04  proff_fs
	* VISUALC6/Doom.dsp:
	* src/gl_main.c:
	* src/m_misc.c:
	* src/r_main.c:
		Added gl_drawskys and gl_sortsprites to config file.
		Implemented sprite sorting in OpenGL.
		Implemented rendering stats for OpenGL.

	* TODO:
		Updated

2000-10-03  proff_fs
	* src/SDL/i_video.c:
	* src/d_main.c:
	* src/gl_intern.h:
	* src/gl_main.c:
	* src/gl_texture.c:
	* src/m_misc.c:
		Put the following variables into the config file: gl_nearclip, gl_farclip, gl_colorbuffer_bits, gl_depthbuffer_bits, gl_tex_filter_string, gl_tex_format_string
		Improved the texture quality by using 5 bits for the colors and 1 bit for alpha. Now colorgradients are much better.
		Renamed boom.cfg to glboom.cfg for the OpenGL version, because of the additional config variables which would get lost when PrBoom is started.

2000-10-02  cph
	* src/doomstat.h:
	* src/g_game.c:
	* src/p_map.c:
	* src/p_mobj.c:
		Fix linuxdoom-1.10 demo sync bug :-) (lost soul bug in P_ZMovement)
		Add new compatibility level
		Fix bug in P_CreateSecNodeList (use of global variable tmthing
		 could overlap with other functions' use of it)
		 (compatibility optioned)

2000-09-30  proff_fs
	* src/i_udp_sdl.c:
		PrBoom should now compile without SDL_net

	* README:
	* VISUALC6/Doom.dsp:
	* src/SDL/i_sound.c:
	* src/qmus2mid.c:
	* src/qmus2mid.h:
		Updated what's new in readme
		Removed qmus2mid.* because we use mmus2mid.*

	* src/SDL/i_video.c:
	* src/doomdata.h:
	* src/gl_main.c:
	* src/p_setup.c:
	* src/r_bsp.c:
	* src/r_defs.h:
	* src/r_main.c:
	* src/r_things.c:
	* src/r_things.h:
		Improved the rendering in OpenGL.
		Translucent segs were drawn more than once.
		Rendered arrays aren't set to 0 every frame, instead a new value "rendermarker" is used.
		Sprites are drawn correctly behind translucent walls.
		To fix:
		In r_bsp.c are some lines missing that were there before I added Figgis changes.
		Some special effects don't work with gl_nodes
		Sprites need to be sorted.

	* VISUALC5/Doom.dsp:
	* src/gl_main.c:
	* src/p_setup.c:
	* src/r_bsp.c:
	* src/r_defs.h:
	* src/r_segs.c:
	* src/r_things.c:
		Sector special effects work for both OldBSP and glBSP nodes.
		Shadow sprites like spectres are drawn a bit more transparent to be more like the original Doom.
		Cleaned up some unecessary leftovers of Figgis glBSP additions.

	* VISUALC6/Doom.dsp:
	* config.h:
	* src/SDL/i_video.c:
	* src/gl_main.c:
	* src/gl_struct.h:
	* src/gl_texture.c:
	* src/m_misc.c:
	* src/p_setup.c:
	* src/r_bsp.c:
	* src/r_main.c:
	* src/r_segs.c:
	* src/r_things.c:
	* src/z_zone.c:
		Fixed some small bugs.
		Added use_mipmapping to cfg-file.
		Tried to fix the sprite in the floor bug, but it just doesn't work.

2000-09-29  proff_fs
	* src/gl_main.c:
	* src/p_setup.c:
		Fixed texture offset bug when using glnodes.

	* VISUALC6/Doom.dsp:
	* src/gl_main.c:
	* src/gl_struct.h:
	* src/r_bsp.c:
	* src/r_main.c:
	* src/r_segs.c:
		If glNodes are used only the subsectors which are visible are drawn, not the entire sector. That speeds up the rendering speed a little bit.
		Since SDL 1.1.5 is finally out, I changed the VisualC project files so the runtime dlls are used.

2000-09-27  proff_fs
	* src/gl_main.c:
	* src/p_setup.c:
	* src/w_wad.c:
